Kariobangi Sharks maintained their unbeaten start to the 2018/2019 SportPesa Premier League when they came from behind to draw 1-1 with Zoo Kericho at Kericho Green Stadium on Thurday. Zoo forward BernardÂ Odhiambo broke the deadlock after 24 minutes after being played in by skipper Johnson Ligare but they could not hold onto the lead to bag a famous victory as Sharks equalised with four minutes remaining on the clock through Sven Yidah. The draw sees Zoo remain stationary at 15th position with seven points while Sharks climb to fourth with 14 points. More to follow...  